<item>
            <title>[LU-19751] kernel update [RHEL 10.1 6.12.0-124.28.1.el10_1]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19751</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es) for kernel 6.12.0-124.21.1.el10_1:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: clone_private_mnt(): make sure that caller has CAP_SYS_ADMIN in the right userns (CVE-2025-38499)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: net: tun: Update napi-&amp;gt;skb after XDP process (CVE-2025-39984)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---10/x86_64/RHSA-2025:23279&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---10/x86_64/RHSA-2025:23279&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es) for kernel 6.12.0-124.28.1.el10_1:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: libceph: fix potential use-after-free in have_mon_and_osd_map() (CVE-2025-68285)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---10/x86_64/RHSA-2026:0786&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---10/x86_64/RHSA-2026:0786&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
